buses, patterns, and envelopes<br/>- recipes are discoverable from curriculum/reference docs<br/>- tests verify recipe files and required labels exist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Tier:** T2 — Standard (New feature / moderate refactoring)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRead the project's ADP documentation and understand existing patterns before making changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**ADP Phases:** Explore → Specify → Test → Implement → Verify → Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 0: Explore\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Read all files in the affected area of the codebase.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Identify existing patterns, naming conventions, and architectural decisions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Review related tests to understand expected behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update progress.md with exploration findings.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 1: Specify\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Write a specification to `specs/t-022@20260416t054258z-spec.md`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Include: problem statement, technical approach, edge cases, acceptance criteria.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Each acceptance criterion must have a VERIFY command.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 2: Test Development\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Write tests BEFORE implementation, derived from the specification.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Tests must FAIL before implementation (Red phase).\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- After this phase, test files are LOCKED — do not modify assertions.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 3: Implement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Implement the minimum code needed to pass all tests.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- One sub-task at a time, commit each logical unit.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Type hints on all function signatures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Follow existing patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Phase 4: Verify & Document\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Run full test suite and quality checks.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Update CHANGELOG.md, progress.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## R